Quote:  Two shifts a day she [sc. the mine-horse] would drag upwards of 200 half-tonne boxes, six at a time, into the lay-by, where Frank ... would jig them down to the next level. [41] About once every three months she would ... [run] wide on one of the corners in such a way as to pull all the boxes off the line.
